Command Codes EFTNT, EFTAD and EFTOF for Electronic
(1) The command codes EFTAD, EFTNT, and EFTOF are used by Collection
personnel in the Campuses to research Electronic Fund Transfers (EFT) infor-
mation, to input new bank information, and to stop an EFT request to the bank.
Command Code EFTNT is used for entering new DDIA EFT bank infor-
mation or changing existing bank information.
Command Code EFTAD is used to obtain bank information and
payment data. It can also display payments for a speciﬁed date or
Command Code EFTOF is used to skip an Electronic Funds Transfer
request to the bank for a speciﬁed TIN and installment date.
Systemic EFTs can be generated by Online Pay System (OPA) and the
Voice Balance Due Interactive Host System (VBD) using Multi-
Functional Equipment (MFE) command codes VREFN, VREFD, and
VREOF. IDRS is equipped, upon command, to perform various tasks
associated with the Electronic Fund Transfers.
(2) Purpose: This transmits revised IRM 2.4.33, IDRS Terminal Input, Command
Codes EFTNT, EFTAD and EFTOF for Electronic Funds Transfer.
(3) Audience: LMSB, SB/SE, TE/GE, and W&I.
(5) Primary Stakeholders: Large Business and International (LB&I), Small
Business Self Employed (SB/SE), Tax Exempt and Government Entities (TE/
